text: Claudia Lösch (born 19 October 1988) is a skier athlete from Austria. She has a disability. She skied at the 2011 IPC Alpine Skiing World Championships. She was the third skier to finish in the sitting women's downhill race and the Super G race. She was the second skier to finish the Super Combined race, Slalom race and Giant Slalom race. ==References== Category:1988 births Category:Living people Category:Competitors at the 2018 Winter Paralympics Category:Austrian skiers Category:Sportspeople from Vienna
